{"parse":{"title":"Congress of Black Writers and Artists","pageid":25272820,"revid":851323968,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Congress of Black Writers and Artists</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/French_language\" title=\"French language\">French</a>: <i>Congr\u00e8s des \u00e9crivains et artistes noirs</i>; originally called the <b>Congress of Negro Writers and Artists</b>) was a meeting of leading <a href=\"/wiki/Black_people\" title=\"Black people\">black</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Intellectual\" title=\"Intellectual\">intellectuals</a> for the purpose of addressing the issues of <a href=\"/wiki/Colonialism\" title=\"Colonialism\">colonialism</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Slavery\" title=\"Slavery\">slavery</a>, and <i><a href=\"/wiki/N%C3%A9gritude\" title=\"N\u00e9gritude\">N\u00e9gritude</a></i>. The First Congress of Black Writers and Artists was organized by the <a href=\"/wiki/Pan-Africanism\" title=\"Pan-Africanism\">Pan-African</a> quarterly cultural, political, and <a href=\"/wiki/Literary_magazine\" title=\"Literary magazine\">literary review</a> <i><a href=\"/wiki/Pr%C3%A9sence_Africaine\" title=\"Pr\u00e9sence Africaine\">Pr\u00e9sence Africaine</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> It was held in <a href=\"/wiki/Paris\" title=\"Paris\">Paris</a> in September 1956.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/wiki/Ahmed_S%C3%A9kou_Tour%C3%A9\" title=\"Ahmed S\u00e9kou Tour\u00e9\">Ahmed S\u00e9kou Tour\u00e9</a> spoke at the Second Congress of Black Writers and Artists, which was held in <a href=\"/wiki/Rome\" title=\"Rome\">Rome</a> in 1959.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Congress_of_Black_Writers_and_Artists&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\"><a href=\"/wiki/Carole_Boyce_Davies\" title=\"Carole Boyce Davies\">Carole Boyce Davies</a> (2008). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=P9ORpnGJh_IC&amp;lpg=PP1&amp;pg=PP1#v=onepage&amp;q=&amp;f=false\"><i>Encyclopedia of the African Diaspora: Origins, Experiences, and Culture</i></a>. <b>1</b>. <a href=\"/wiki/ABC-CLIO\" title=\"ABC-CLIO\">ABC-CLIO</a>. p.&#160;767. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1-85109-700-7\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1-85109-700-7\">1-85109-700-7</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Encyclopedia+of+the+African+Diaspora%3A+Origins%2C+Experiences%2C+and+Culture&amp;rft.pages=767&amp;rft.pub=ABC-CLIO&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.isbn=1-85109-700-7&amp;rft.au=Carole+Boyce+Davies&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DP9ORpnGJh_IC%26lpg%3DPP1%26pg%3DPP1%23v%3Donepage%26q%3D%26f%3Dfalse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACongress+of+Black+Writers+and+Artists\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Richard H. King (2004). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=kIZ2pAGyNYUC&amp;lpg=PP1&amp;pg=PP1#v=onepage&amp;q=&amp;f=false\"><i>Race, Culture, and the Intellectuals, 1940-1970</i></a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Woodrow_Wilson_Center_Press\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Woodrow Wilson Center Press\">Woodrow Wilson Center Press</a>. p.&#160;201. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-8018-8066-1\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-8018-8066-1\">0-8018-8066-1</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Race%2C+Culture%2C+and+the+Intellectuals%2C+1940-1970&amp;rft.pages=201&amp;rft.pub=Woodrow+Wilson+Center+Press&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.isbn=0-8018-8066-1&amp;rft.au=Richard+H.+King&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DkIZ2pAGyNYUC%26lpg%3DPP1%26pg%3DPP1%23v%3Donepage%26q%3D%26f%3Dfalse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACongress+of+Black+Writers+and+Artists\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Robert William July (1987). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=qF-QpNA2QqYC&amp;lpg=PP1&amp;pg=PP1#v=onepage&amp;q=&amp;f=false\"><i>An African Voice: The Role of the Humanities in African Independence</i></a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Duke_University_Press\" title=\"Duke University Press\">Duke University Press</a>. p.&#160;24. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-8223-0769-3\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-8223-0769-3\">0-8223-0769-3</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=An+African+Voice%3A+The+Role+of+the+Humanities+in+African+I